[2.809585, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m  ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════╗\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[1m  ║          \u001b[36mCALORON\u001b[0m\u001b[1m — Multi-Agent Sprint         ║\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[1m  ║    Agents collaborate through Git to build   ║\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[1m  ║               software autonomously          ║\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[1m  ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════╝\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[4.813465, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[36m▸ Goal: Build a Python hotel rate anomaly detector for an OTA revenue management team. Given a CSV of daily hotel rates (hotel_id, date, rate, occupancy_pct), detect pricing anomalies using z-score with seasonal adjustment. Flag rates deviating more than 2 std from rolling mean. Return summaries with hotel_id, date, rate, expected_rate, z_score, is_anomaly. Include pytest tests.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[6.826629, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[36m▸ Step 1: PO Agent plans the sprint\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[50.95802, "o", "  1. Implement hotel rate anomaly detector with seasonal z-score\r\n     depends on: none\r\n  2. Generate sample CSV with known anomalies for testing\r\n     depends on: none\r\n  3. Write pytest tests for all anomaly detector functions\r\n     depends on: 1-core-detector, 2-sample-data\r\n"]
